2026-02-20 10:11:17 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are an expert Travel Planner assistant specializing in creating detailed holiday itineraries.\n\nYour role is to:\n1. Create a comprehensive day-by-day travel plan based on the user's destination country and number of days\n2. Suggest popular tourist attractions and activities for each day\n3. Recommend suitable hotels with different budget categories (budget, mid-range, luxury)\n4. Calculate approximate budget breakdown including:\n   - Accommodation costs per night\n   - Daily food expenses\n   - Transportation costs\n   - Attraction entry fees\n   - Total estimated trip cost\n\nInput from user: Country/City and Number of Days\n\nOutput format:\n- Day-by-day itinerary with morning, afternoon, and evening activities\n- Hotel suggestions with approximate prices\n- Budget calculator with itemized costs\n- Travel tips and recommendations\n\nBe specific, practical, and provide realistic time estimates for each activity.", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-abcd4a3b-c694-4dbf-aeb8-885c58c92ab7", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 (INR) max  \n*(All prices are approximate, based on 2024 rates and mid\u2011season travel. Convert to your own currency if needed.)*  \n\n---\n\n### QUICK OVERVIEW  \n\n| Item | Approx. Cost (\u20b9) | Notes |\n|------|------------------|-------|\n| **Flights / Train (to Goa)** | 6\u202f000 \u2013 12\u202f000 (round\u2011trip) | From major Indian metros \u2013 low\u2011cost airlines or 2nd\u2011class AC train. |\n| **Accommodation (2 nights)** | 1\u202f500 \u2013 15\u202f000 per night | See three hotel tiers below. |\n| **Food & Drinks** | 800 \u2013 1\u202f200 per day | Breakfast often included; dinner at beach shacks. |\n| **Local Transport** | 350 \u2013 1\u202f200 per day | Scooter rental or Uber/Ola. |\n| **Attraction Fees & Activities** | 500 \u2013 3\u202f000 total | Forts, museums, water\u2011sports, sunset cruise. |\n| **Miscellaneous (souvenirs, tips, taxes)** | 1\u202f000 \u2013 2\u202f000 | |\n| **Total (budget\u2011friendly)** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f15\u202f000 \u2013 35\u202f000** | Well under the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 ceiling, leaving room for upgrades or extra splurges. |\n\nBelow is a **day\u2011by\u2011day itinerary** (morning\u2011afternoon\u2011evening) that works for any of the three accommodation budgets. Pick the hotel tier that fits your style and adjust food/activities accordingly.\n\n---\n\n## DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n### **Day\u202f1 \u2013 Arrival, North Goa Highlights**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Time Needed |\n|------|----------|-----------------------|\n| **08:00 \u2013 09:30** | **Travel to Goa** | Arrive at Dabolim Airport (or Thivim Railway Station). Pre\u2011book a **airport\u2011to\u2011hotel transfer** (\u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f500) or grab an Uber. |\n| **09:30 \u2013 10:30** | **Check\u2011in & Freshen up** | Drop luggage, freshen up. If you booked a **budget/hostel**, most include **free breakfast** (continental/Indian). |\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beach** | Walk or scooter to the beach. Sunbathe, dip in the sea, try a quick **water\u2011sports session** (parasailing \u20b9\u202f800, banana boat \u20b9\u202f400). |\n| **12:30 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch** | Beach shack \u2013 **Goan fish thali** (\u20b9\u202f250\u2011\u20b9\u202f350). |\n| **13:30 \u2013 15:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | 15\u2011min scooter ride. Entry is free; small donation for maintenance (\u20b9\u202f20). Great photo spots. |\n| **15:30 \u2013 16:30** | **Coffee Break** | Caf\u00e9 at **Caf\u00e9 Chocolatti** (Baga) \u2013 coffee + pastry (\u20b9\u202f150). |\n| **16:30 \u2013 18:30** | **Anjuna Flea Market** *(Saturday only)* or **Mapusa Market** (daily) | Shop for handicrafts, spices, beachwear. Bargain! |\n| **18:30 \u2013 20:00** | **Sunset at Chapora Fort** | Short hike (20\u202fmin). Entry free. Best views of Vagator Beach. |\n| **20:00 \u2013 22:00** | **Dinner & Nightlife** | Dinner at **Thalassa** (Greek/Goan fusion) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f600\u2011\u20b9\u202f900 per person. If you prefer a quieter night, try **Mango Tree** in Calangute. |\n| **22:00** | **Return to hotel** | Relax, early night (or explore the lively Baga bar strip). |\n\n---\n\n### **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa Relaxation & Culture**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Time Needed |\n|------|----------|-----------------------|\n| **07:30 \u2013 08:30** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (budget hostels often include) or **Caf\u00e9 Bomra\u2019s** (Panjim) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f150\u2011\u20b9\u202f250. |\n| **08:30 \u2013 10:30** | **Old Goa Churches** | Taxi or scooter to **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus** (UNESCO) \u2013 entry free, donation \u20b9\u202f20. Follow with **Se Cathedral** (free). |\n| **10:30 \u2013 11:30** | **Museum of Christian Art** (optional) | Entry \u20b9\u202f50. |\n| **11:30 \u2013 13:00** | **Miramar Beach & Panjim Walk** | Stroll along the promenade, snap photos of the **Rashtriya\u202fRavivar** (government) building. |\n| **13:00 \u2013 14:00** | **Lunch** | **Mum\u2019s Kitchen** (authentic Goan) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f450. |\n| **14:00 \u2013 16:00** | **Colva / Benaulim Beach** | Relax, optional **kayak** (\u20b9\u202f500) or **shark\u2011spotting boat ride** (\u20b9\u202f800). |\n| **16:00 \u2013 17:00** | **Coconut Grove & Sunset at Palolem** (if you\u2019re up for a 1\u2011hr drive) | Otherwise stay at **Cavelossim** for a quieter sunset. |\n| **17:30 \u2013 19:00** | **Evening at a Beach Shack** | Try **Fisherman\u2019s Wharf** (Cavelossim) \u2013 fresh prawns, live music. |\n| **19:30 \u2013 21:00** | **Dinner** | **Martin\u2019s Corner** (Betalbatim) \u2013 famous for Goan crab (\u20b9\u202f700\u2011\u20b9\u202f1\u202f000). |\n| **21:30** | **Return to hotel, pack** | Prepare for departure next morning. |\n\n*If your flight/train leaves late night, you can swap dinner with a night\u2011cap at a beach bar and head straight to the airport.*\n\n---\n\n## HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Category | Property (Area) | Approx. Price per Night (\u20b9) | What\u2019s Included | Why It\u2019s Good for This Trip |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------------------|-----------------|----------------------------|\n| **Budget** | **Zostel Goa \u2013 Calangute** | 1\u202f500 \u2013 2\u202f200 (dorm) / 2\u202f800 \u2013 3\u202f500 (private) | Free Wi\u2011Fi, breakfast (optional), common kitchen | Central to North\u2011Goa beaches, great for meeting other travelers. |\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Fern Residency \u2013 Candolim** | 4\u202f000 \u2013 5\u202f500 | Breakfast, pool, sea\u2011view rooms, Wi\u2011Fi | Quiet, close to both North & South attractions, good value. |\n| **Luxury** | **Alila Diwa Goa \u2013 Majorda** | 13\u202f000 \u2013 15\u202f000 | All\u2011meals (optional), spa, infinity pool, beachfront | Premium service, perfect for a splurge while staying under \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 total. |\n\n*All three hotels are within 10\u201115\u202fmin drive of the Day\u20111 beach circuit and 45\u201160\u202fmin of South\u2011Goa sites.*\n\n---\n\n## BUDGET CALCULATOR (Example: Mid\u2011Range Stay)\n\n| Item | Qty | Unit Cost (\u20b9) | Sub\u2011Total (\u20b9) | Notes |\n|------|-----|---------------|---------------|-------|\n| **Round\u2011trip flight (e.g., Delhi\u2011Goa, low\u2011cost)** | 1 | 7\u202f000 | 7\u202f000 | Book 4\u20116\u202fweeks early for best fare. |\n| **Accommodation (The Fern Residency)** | 2 nights | 4\u202f500 | 9\u202f000 | Includes breakfast. |\n| **Food & Drinks** | 2 days | 1\u202f000 | 2\u202f000 | Lunch & dinner (breakfast covered). |\n| **Local transport \u2013 scooter rental** | 2 days | 350 | 700 | Helmet included; fuel extra ~\u20b9\u202f150. |\n| **Airport\u2011hotel transfers (taxi/Uber)** | 2 trips | 400 | 800 | Approx. \u20b9\u202f200 each way. |\n| **Attraction fees & activities** | \u2013 | \u2013 | 2\u202f200 | Fort Aguada (\u20b9\u202f20), water\u2011sports (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200), church donations (\u20b9\u202f50), sunset cruise (\u20b9\u202f800). |\n| **Miscellaneous (souvenirs, tips, taxes)** | \u2013 | \u2013 | 1\u202f200 | |\n| **Total** | \u2013 | \u2013 | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f22\u202f900** | Well under the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 ceiling \u2013 you can upgrade to luxury, add more water\u2011sports, or keep the extra cash for shopping. |\n\n### If you choose **Luxury** (Alila Diwa)\n\n| Item | Qty | Unit Cost (\u20b9) | Sub\u2011Total (\u20b9) |\n|------|-----|---------------|---------------|\n| Flights | 1 | 7\u202f000 | 7\u202f000 |\n| Accommodation (Alila) | 2 nights | 14\u202f000 | 28\u202f000 |\n| Food & Drinks (incl. 2\u2011meal plan) | 2 days | 1\u202f500 | 3\u202f000 |\n| Transport (scooter + occasional Uber) | 2 days | 800 | 1\u202f600 |\n| Activities (spa, water\u2011sports, cruise) | \u2013 | \u2013 | 4\u202f000 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u2013 | \u2013 | 1\u202f500 |\n| **Grand Total** | \u2013 | \u2013 | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f45\u202f100** |\n\nYou still have ~\u20b9\u202f5\u202f000 left for extra shopping or a night\u2011out.\n\n---\n\n## TRAVEL TIPS & RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n1. **Best Time to Visit** \u2013 October\u202f\u2013\u202fMarch (dry, pleasant weather).  \n2. **Getting Around** \u2013 A **scooter** is the cheapest and most flexible way to explore. Carry a valid driving licence and wear a helmet (mandatory).  \n3. **Cash vs Card** \u2013 Most beach shacks accept cash only; keep \u20b9\u202f2\u202f000\u2011\u20b9\u202f3\u202f000 in small notes for tips and small purchases. Larger restaurants and hotels accept cards.  \n4. **Sun Protection** \u2013 Sunscreen SPF\u202f30+, sunglasses, and a hat are essential; the sun can be intense even in winter.  \n5. **Safety** \u2013 Goa is generally safe, but keep an eye on belongings on crowded beaches and markets. Avoid isolated beaches after dark.  \n6. **Local Cuisine** \u2013 Try **Goan fish curry**, **prawn balch\u00e3o**, **bebinca** (dessert), and the famous **feni** (cashew or coconut spirit).  \n7. **Cultural Etiquette** \u2013 When visiting churches, dress modestly (cover shoulders/knees). Remove shoes before entering.  \n8. **Connectivity** \u2013 Buy a prepaid **Jio/ Airtel** SIM at the airport (\u20b9\u202f200 for 10\u202fGB data).  \n9. **Packing List** \u2013 Light cotton clothes, swimwear, flip\u2011flops, comfortable walking shoes, a small day\u2011backpack, reusable water bottle.  \n\n---\n\n### QUICK CHECKLIST BEFORE YOU GO  \n\n- [ ] Book flights/train **2\u20113\u202fweeks** in advance (price lock).  \n- [ ] Reserve your chosen hotel (most sites allow free cancellation).  \n- [ ] Pre\u2011pay scooter rental (many agencies allow online booking).  \n- [ ] Pack a **dry\u2011bag** for electronics (beach sand & water).  \n- [ ] Print or screenshot e\u2011tickets, hotel confirmation, and a map of Goa (offline Google Maps).  \n\n---\n\n## FINAL WORD  \n\nWith a **\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000** budget you can comfortably enjoy **both the lively North\u2011Goa scene and the tranquil South\u2011Goa coastline**, stay in a **mid\u2011range hotel** (or splurge on a luxury beachfront resort), and still have plenty left for **delicious food, a few water\u2011sports, and souvenirs**.  \n\nFeel free to let me know which hotel tier you prefer or if you\u2019d like to add any specific experiences (e.g., scuba diving, spice plantation tour, night market). I can fine\u2011tune the itinerary and provide booking links! Happy travels! \ud83c\udf34\u2708\ufe0f", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": null, "reasoning": "We need to produce a two-day itinerary for Goa, with budget of 50000 (presumably INR). Provide day-by-day plan, hotel suggestions (budget, mid-range, luxury) with approximate prices, budget calculator itemized, travel tips. Must be realistic. Provide morning, afternoon, evening activities. Also include transportation costs, food, attractions entry fees. Need to keep total within 50000 INR. Provide suggestions for staying within budget.\n\nWe need to assume user is traveling from somewhere (maybe India). Provide options for arrival (e.g., flight or train). Provide approximate costs.\n\nLet's craft.\n\nWe need to be careful to not violate policy. It's fine.\n\nWe'll produce:\n\n- Overview\n- Day 1: Morning (arrival, check-in, breakfast, beach), etc.\n- Day 2: similar.\n\nHotel suggestions: budget (e.g., Zostel, ~1500 INR/night), mid-range (e.g., Taj Exotica? That's luxury; mid-range maybe The Fern, ~4000), luxury (e.g., Alila, ~15000). Provide price per night.\n\nBudget breakdown: accommodation (choose one category maybe mid-range), food (\u20b9800 per day), transport (rental scooter \u20b9350 per day, or taxi), attractions (entry fees: e.g., Fort Aguada \u20b920, etc). Total.\n\nWe need to keep total <= 50000.\n\nLet's compute:\n\nOption: mid-range hotel 4000 per night x2 = 8000.\n\nFood: 800 per day x2 = 1600.\n\nTransport: scooter 350 per day x2 = 700; plus airport transfers 500 each way = 1000.\n\nAttractions: entry fees maybe 500 total.\n\nTotal = 8000+1600+700+1000+500 = 11800. That's far below 50000, leaving room for extra activities, maybe water sports.\n\nBut we can also give luxury option: 15000 per night x2 = 30000, plus other costs ~5000 = 35000, still within 50000.\n\nWe'll present three budget categories.\n\nAlso include suggestions for meals, local transport, etc.\n\nLet's craft final answer."}}], "created": 1771562480, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "on_demand", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8a618bed98", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 3158, "prompt_tokens": 272, "total_tokens": 3430, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 450, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": null, "queue_time": 0.048044183, "prompt_time": 0.016682646, "completion_time": 6.729725492, "total_time": 6.746408138}, "usage_breakdown": null, "x_groq": {"id": "req_01khwnm6enf6b9063pbwqvx3tj", "seed": 1846612767}}, "prompt_tokens": 272, "completion_tokens": 3158, "agent_id": "Travel_Planner_c5585e0a-0833-4e4d-a341-f77a11bf0c5b/c5585e0a-0833-4e4d-a341-f77a11bf0c5b"}
2026-02-20 10:11:17 - INFO - 405 -Publishing message of type GroupChatMessage to all subscribers: {'message': TextMessage(id='a51606dc-0729-4990-9c29-8318847da81e', source='Travel_Planner', models_usage=RequestUsage(prompt_tokens=272, completion_tokens=3158), metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 2, 20, 4, 41, 17, 399293, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content='## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway –\u202f\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 (INR) max  \n*(All prices are approximate, based on 2024 rates and mid\u2011season travel. Convert to your own currency if needed.)*  \n\n---\n\n### QUICK OVERVIEW  \n\n| Item | Approx. Cost (\u20b9) | Notes |\n|------|------------------|-------|\n| **Flights / Train (to Goa)** | 6\u202f000 – 12\u202f000 (round\u2011trip) | From major Indian metros – low\u2011cost airlines or 2nd\u2011class AC train. |\n| **Accommodation (2 nights)** | 1\u202f500 – 15\u202f000 per night | See three hotel tiers below. |\n| **Food & Drinks** | 800 – 1\u202f200 per day | Breakfast often included; dinner at beach shacks. |\n| **Local Transport** | 350 – 1\u202f200 per day | Scooter rental or Uber/Ola. |\n| **Attraction Fees & Activities** | 500 – 3\u202f000 total | Forts, museums, water\u2011sports, sunset cruise. |\n| **Miscellaneous (souvenirs, tips, taxes)** | 1\u202f000 – 2\u202f000 | |\n| **Total (budget\u2011friendly)** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f15\u202f000 – 35\u202f000** | Well under the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 ceiling, leaving room for upgrades or extra splurges. |\n\nBelow is a **day\u2011by\u2011day itinerary** (morning\u2011afternoon\u2011evening) that works for any of the three accommodation budgets. Pick the hotel tier that fits your style and adjust food/activities accordingly.\n\n---\n\n## DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n### **Day\u202f1 – Arrival, North Goa Highlights**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Time Needed |\n|------|----------|-----------------------|\n| **08:00 – 09:30** | **Travel to Goa** | Arrive at Dabolim Airport (or Thivim Railway Station). Pre\u2011book a **airport\u2011to\u2011hotel transfer** (\u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f500) or grab an Uber. |\n| **09:30 – 10:30** | **Check\u2011in & Freshen up** | Drop luggage, freshen up. If you booked a **budget/hostel**, most include **free breakfast** (continental/Indian). |\n| **10:30 – 12:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beach** | Walk or scooter to the beach. Sunbathe, dip in the sea, try a quick **water\u2011sports session** (parasailing \u20b9\u202f800, banana boat \u20b9\u202f400). |\n| **12:30 – 13:30** | **Lunch** | Beach shack – **Goan fish thali** (\u20b9\u202f250\u2011\u20b9\u202f350). |\n| **13:30 – 15:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | 15\u2011min scooter ride. Entry is free; small donation for maintenance (\u20b9\u202f20). Great photo spots. |\n| **15:30 – 16:30** | **Coffee Break** | Café at **Café Chocolatti** (Baga) – coffee + pastry (\u20b9\u202f150). |\n| **16:30 – 18:30** | **Anjuna Flea Market** *(Saturday only)* or **Mapusa Market** (daily) | Shop for handicrafts, spices, beachwear. Bargain! |\n| **18:30 – 20:00** | **Sunset at Chapora Fort** | Short hike (20\u202fmin). Entry free. Best views of Vagator Beach. |\n| **20:00 – 22:00** | **Dinner & Nightlife** | Dinner at **Thalassa** (Greek/Goan fusion) – \u20b9\u202f600\u2011\u20b9\u202f900 per person. If you prefer a quieter night, try **Mango Tree** in Calangute. |\n| **22:00** | **Return to hotel** | Relax, early night (or explore the lively Baga bar strip). |\n\n---\n\n### **Day\u202f2 – South Goa Relaxation & Culture**\n\n| Time | Activity | Details & Time Needed |\n|------|----------|-----------------------|\n| **07:30 – 08:30** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (budget hostels often include) or **Café Bomra’s** (Panjim) – \u20b9\u202f150\u2011\u20b9\u202f250. |\n| **08:30 – 10:30** | **Old Goa Churches** | Taxi or scooter to **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus** (UNESCO) – entry free, donation \u20b9\u202f20. Follow with **Se Cathedral** (free). |\n| **10:30 – 11:30** | **Museum of Christian Art** (optional) | Entry \u20b9\u202f50. |\n| **11:30 – 13:00** | **Miramar Beach & Panjim Walk** | Stroll along the promenade, snap photos of the **Rashtriya\u202fRavivar** (government) building. |\n| **13:00 – 14:00** | **Lunch** | **Mum’s Kitchen** (authentic Goan) – \u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f450. |\n| **14:00 – 16:00** | **Colva / Benaulim Beach** | Relax, optional **kayak** (\u20b9\u202f500) or **shark\u2011spotting boat ride** (\u20b9\u202f800). |\n| **16:00 – 17:00** | **Coconut Grove & Sunset at Palolem** (if you’re up for a 1\u2011hr drive) | Otherwise stay at **Cavelossim** for a quieter sunset. |\n| **17:30 – 19:00** | **Evening at a Beach Shack** | Try **Fisherman’s Wharf** (Cavelossim) – fresh prawns, live music. |\n| **19:30 – 21:00** | **Dinner** | **Martin’s Corner** (Betalbatim) – famous for Goan crab (\u20b9\u202f700\u2011\u20b9\u202f1\u202f000). |\n| **21:30** | **Return to hotel, pack** | Prepare for departure next morning. |\n\n*If your flight/train leaves late night, you can swap dinner with a night\u2011cap at a beach bar and head straight to the airport.*\n\n---\n\n## HOTEL RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n| Category | Property (Area) | Approx. Price per Night (\u20b9) | What’s Included | Why It’s Good for This Trip |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------------------|-----------------|----------------------------|\n| **Budget** | **Zostel Goa – Calangute** | 1\u202f500 – 2\u202f200 (dorm) / 2\u202f800 – 3\u202f500 (private) | Free Wi\u2011Fi, breakfast (optional), common kitchen | Central to North\u2011Goa beaches, great for meeting other travelers. |\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Fern Residency – Candolim** | 4\u202f000 – 5\u202f500 | Breakfast, pool, sea\u2011view rooms, Wi\u2011Fi | Quiet, close to both North & South attractions, good value. |\n| **Luxury** | **Alila Diwa Goa – Majorda** | 13\u202f000 – 15\u202f000 | All\u2011meals (optional), spa, infinity pool, beachfront | Premium service, perfect for a splurge while staying under \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 total. |\n\n*All three hotels are within 10\u201115\u202fmin drive of the Day\u20111 beach circuit and 45\u201160\u202fmin of South\u2011Goa sites.*\n\n---\n\n## BUDGET CALCULATOR (Example: Mid\u2011Range Stay)\n\n| Item | Qty | Unit Cost (\u20b9) | Sub\u2011Total (\u20b9) | Notes |\n|------|-----|---------------|---------------|-------|\n| **Round\u2011trip flight (e.g., Delhi\u2011Goa, low\u2011cost)** | 1 | 7\u202f000 | 7\u202f000 | Book 4\u20116\u202fweeks early for best fare. |\n| **Accommodation (The Fern Residency)** | 2 nights | 4\u202f500 | 9\u202f000 | Includes breakfast. |\n| **Food & Drinks** | 2 days | 1\u202f000 | 2\u202f000 | Lunch & dinner (breakfast covered). |\n| **Local transport – scooter rental** | 2 days | 350 | 700 | Helmet included; fuel extra ~\u20b9\u202f150. |\n| **Airport\u2011hotel transfers (taxi/Uber)** | 2 trips | 400 | 800 | Approx. \u20b9\u202f200 each way. |\n| **Attraction fees & activities** | – | – | 2\u202f200 | Fort Aguada (\u20b9\u202f20), water\u2011sports (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200), church donations (\u20b9\u202f50), sunset cruise (\u20b9\u202f800). |\n| **Miscellaneous (souvenirs, tips, taxes)** | – | – | 1\u202f200 | |\n| **Total** | – | – | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f22\u202f900** | Well under the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 ceiling – you can upgrade to luxury, add more water\u2011sports, or keep the extra cash for shopping. |\n\n### If you choose **Luxury** (Alila Diwa)\n\n| Item | Qty | Unit Cost (\u20b9) | Sub\u2011Total (\u20b9) |\n|------|-----|---------------|---------------|\n| Flights | 1 | 7\u202f000 | 7\u202f000 |\n| Accommodation (Alila) | 2 nights | 14\u202f000 | 28\u202f000 |\n| Food & Drinks (incl. 2\u2011meal plan) | 2 days | 1\u202f500 | 3\u202f000 |\n| Transport (scooter + occasional Uber) | 2 days | 800 | 1\u202f600 |\n| Activities (spa, water\u2011sports, cruise) | – | – | 4\u202f000 |\n| Miscellaneous | – | – | 1\u202f500 |\n| **Grand Total** | – | – | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f45\u202f100** |\n\nYou still have ~\u20b9\u202f5\u202f000 left for extra shopping or a night\u2011out.\n\n---\n\n## TRAVEL TIPS & RECOMMENDATIONS  \n\n1. **Best Time to Visit** – October\u202f–\u202fMarch (dry, pleasant weather).  \n2. **Getting Around** – A **scooter** is the cheapest and most flexible way to explore. Carry a valid driving licence and wear a helmet (mandatory).  \n3. **Cash vs Card** – Most beach shacks accept cash only; keep \u20b9\u202f2\u202f000\u2011\u20b9\u202f3\u202f000 in small notes for tips and small purchases. Larger restaurants and hotels accept cards.  \n4. **Sun Protection** – Sunscreen SPF\u202f30+, sunglasses, and a hat are essential; the sun can be intense even in winter.  \n5. **Safety** – Goa is generally safe, but keep an eye on belongings on crowded beaches and markets. Avoid isolated beaches after dark.  \n6. **Local Cuisine** – Try **Goan fish curry**, **prawn balchăo**, **bebinca** (dessert), and the famous **feni** (cashew or coconut spirit).  \n7. **Cultural Etiquette** – When visiting churches, dress modestly (cover shoulders/knees). Remove shoes before entering.  \n8. **Connectivity** – Buy a prepaid **Jio/ Airtel** SIM at the airport (\u20b9\u202f200 for 10\u202fGB data).  \n9. **Packing List** – Light cotton clothes, swimwear, flip\u2011flops, comfortable walking shoes, a small day\u2011backpack, reusable water bottle.  \n\n---\n\n### QUICK CHECKLIST BEFORE YOU GO  \n\n- [ ] Book flights/train **2\u20113\u202fweeks** in advance (price lock).  \n- [ ] Reserve your chosen hotel (most sites allow free cancellation).  \n- [ ] Pre\u2011pay scooter rental (many agencies allow online booking).  \n- [ ] Pack a **dry\u2011bag** for electronics (beach sand & water).  \n- [ ] Print or screenshot e\u2011tickets, hotel confirmation, and a map of Goa (offline Google Maps).  \n\n---\n\n## FINAL WORD  \n\nWith a **\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000** budget you can comfortably enjoy **both the lively North\u2011Goa scene and the tranquil South\u2011Goa coastline**, stay in a **mid\u2011range hotel** (or splurge on a luxury beachfront resort), and still have plenty left for **delicious food, a few water\u2011sports, and souvenirs**.  \n\nFeel free to let me know which hotel tier you prefer or if you’d like to add any specific experiences (e.g., scuba diving, spice plantation tour, night market). I can fine\u2011tune the itinerary and provide booking links! Happy travels! \U0001f334\u2708\ufe0f', type='TextMessage')}
