the file.  \\n2. **Restart** the TravelBot service (or re\u2011run the script) so the updated module is loaded.  \\n3. Run a quick sanity check, e.g.:\\n\\n```python\\nfrom HolidayAgent.Tools.GoogleMap import get_coordinates\\nprint(get_coordinates(\\\"Goa, India\\\"))\\n```\\n\\nYou should now either get a proper coordinate dictionary **or** a clear `HolidayAgentException` that includes the underlying error message.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7\ufe0f\u20e3 Common pitfalls & extra tips\\n\\n| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |\\n|---------|--------------|-----|\\n| Still getting the same error after adding a default value | The script is **imported** from a compiled `.pyc` that wasn\u2019t refreshed. | Delete any `__pycache__` folder in `Tools/` and restart the app. |\\n| New error: `NameError: name 'e' is not defined` | You added `error_detail=str(e)` but the `except` clause doesn\u2019t bind the exception to `e`. | Use `except Exception as e:` (or rename accordingly). |\\n| \u201cAPI key invalid\u201d appears in `error_detail` | The Google Maps API key is missing/expired. | Verify `GOOGLE_API_KEY` env variable or config file. |\\n| No response from Google Maps (timeout) | Network/firewall block. | Test the request with `curl` or Postman; ensure outbound HTTPS is allowed. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 8\ufe0f\u20e3 Quick \u201ccopy\u2011paste\u201d patch (if you want to apply it directly)\\n\\n```python\\n# ---- Begin patch ----\\n# File: C:\\\\AI_2026\\\\Projects\\\\1_TravelBot\\\\HolidayAgent\\\\Tools\\\\GoogleMap.py\\n\\n# 1. Update the exception class (if needed)\\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = None):\\n        super().__init__(message)\\n        self.message = message\\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\\n\\n# 2. Locate the raise (likely around line 13) and modify:\\ntry:\\n    # ... your Google Maps request code ...\\nexcept Exception as e:                     # make sure you capture the exception as e\\n    raise HolidayAgentException(\\n        \\\"Failed to fetch location data\\\",\\n        error_detail=str(e)                # now we pass the second argument\\n    )\\n# ---- End patch ----\\n```\\n\\nSave, clear `__pycache__`, and restart.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 9\ufe0f\u20e3 TL;DR Checklist\\n\\n- [ ] Open `GoogleMap.py`.  \\n- [ ] Ensure `HolidayAgentException.__init__` has a default for `error_detail`.  \\n- [ ] In the `except` block, raise the exception **with two arguments** (`message`, `error_detail`).  \\n- [ ] Delete `__pycache__` (or run `python -B` to ignore caches).  \\n- [ ] Restart the bot and test a simple call to the Google Maps helper.  \\n\\n---\\n\\nIf you run into any other traceback lines or need help with the Google Maps API request itself (e.g., handling rate limits, adding retries, or parsing the JSON response), just let me know and I\u2019ll walk you through that as well. Happy debugging! \ud83d\ude80\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"}}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_c5585e0a-0833-4e4d-a341-f77a11bf0c5b/c5585e0a-0833-4e4d-a341-f77a11bf0c5b", "receiver": "output_topic_c5585e0a-0833-4e4d-a341-f77a11bf0c5b/c5585e0a-0833-4e4d-a341-f77a11bf0c5b", "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.SEND", "type": "Message"}
