2026-02-20 10:12:54 - INFO - 574 -{"payload": "{\"response\":{\"chat_message\":{\"id\":\"62a288ac-d056-4de1-8537-dd9cf9caa00b\",\"source\":\"Travel_Planner\",\"models_usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":4535,\"completion_tokens\":2028},\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-20T04:42:54.204559Z\",\"content\":\"## \ud83d\udccd What the error means  \\n\\n```\\nHolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail'\\n```\\n\\nYour custom exception class **expects two arguments** when it is instantiated:\\n\\n```python\\nHolidayAgentException(message, error_detail)\\n```\\n\\nBut somewhere in `GoogleMap.py` (line\u202f13) it is being raised with only the `message` argument, so Python throws the above `TypeError`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \u2705 Two ways to solve it  \\n\\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Make `error_detail` optional (recommended \u2013 safer for the whole project)\\n\\nEdit the definition of `HolidayAgentException` so that `error_detail` has a default value (`None`). Then you can raise the exception with **one** or **two** arguments.\\n\\n```python\\n# C:\\\\AI_2026\\\\Projects\\\\1_TravelBot\\\\HolidayAgent\\\\Tools\\\\GoogleMap.py\\n\\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Custom exception for the HolidayAgent tools.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = None):\\n        super().__init__(message)          # keep the normal Exception behaviour\\n        self.message = message\\n        self.error_detail = error_detail   # may be None if not supplied\\n```\\n\\n*After this change you can keep the existing raise statements unchanged.*\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2\ufe0f\u20e3 Pass the missing argument wherever the exception is raised (quick fix)\\n\\nIf you prefer not to touch the exception class, locate every `raise HolidayAgentException(...)` line (line\u202f13 is the first) and supply a second argument\u2014usually the caught exception\u2019s text.\\n\\n```python\\ntry:\\n    # \u2026 code that calls Google Maps API \u2026\\nexcept Exception as e:                     # <-- capture the original error\\n    raise HolidayAgentException(\\n        \\\"Failed to fetch location data\\\",\\n        error_detail=str(e)                # <-- now we give the second argument\\n    )\\n```\\n\\nYou can also pass any custom string that helps you debug, e.g. `error_detail=\\\"HTTP 403 \u2013 invalid API key\\\"`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udcc2 Full \u201cpatch\u201d you can copy\u2011paste\\n\\nBelow is a **complete, ready\u2011to\u2011paste** version of `GoogleMap.py` that incorporates both fixes (optional `error_detail` **and** a safe raise with details).  \\nReplace the contents of the file with this (or merge the relevant parts).\\n\\n```python\\n# --------------------------------------------------------------\\n# C:\\\\AI_2026\\\\Projects\\\\1_TravelBot\\\\HolidayAgent\\\\Tools\\\\GoogleMap.py\\n# --------------------------------------------------------------\\n\\nimport os\\nimport requests\\nfrom typing import Dict, Tuple\\n\\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------\\n# 1\ufe0f\u20e3  Custom exception \u2013 error_detail is optional (default = None)\\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------\\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Exception raised by HolidayAgent tools.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = None):\\n        super().__init__(message)\\n        self.message = message\\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\\n\\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------\\n# 2\ufe0f\u20e3  Helper to read the Google Maps API key from env / config\\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------\\ndef _get_api_key() -> str:\\n    key = os.getenv(\\\"GOOGLE_API_KEY\\\")\\n    if not key:\\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\\n            \\\"Google Maps API key not found in environment variables\\\",\\n            error_detail=\\\"Set GOOGLE_API_KEY before running the bot\\\"\\n        )\\n    return key\\n\\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------\\n# 3\ufe0f\u20e3  Core function \u2013 fetch latitude/longitude for an address\\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------\\ndef get_coordinates(address: str) -> Tuple[float, float]:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Returns (lat, lng) for the supplied address using Google Geocoding API.\\n    Raises HolidayAgentException with a helpful error_detail on failure.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    api_key = _get_api_key()\\n    endpoint = \\\"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json\\\"\\n\\n    try:\\n        response = requests.get(\\n            endpoint,\\n            params={\\\"address\\\": address, \\\"key\\\": api_key},\\n            timeout=10,\\n        )\\n        response.raise_for_status()               # HTTP errors \u2192 raise\\n        data = response.json()\\n\\n        if data.get(\\\"status\\\") != \\\"OK\\\" or not data.get(\\\"results\\\"):\\n            raise HolidayAgentException(\\n                f\\\"Geocoding API returned no results for '{address}'\\\",\\n                error_detail=f\\\"API status: {data.get('status')}\\\"\\n            )\\n\\n        location = data[\\\"results\\\"][0][\\\"geometry\\\"][\\\"location\\\"]\\n        return float(location[\\\"lat\\\"]), float(location[\\\"lng\\\"])\\n\\n    except requests.RequestException as req_err:\\n        # Network\u2011level problems (timeout, DNS, connection reset, etc.)\\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\\n            \\\"Network error while contacting Google Maps API\\\",\\n            error_detail=str(req_err)\\n        )\\n    except Exception as generic_err:\\n        # Anything else (JSON parsing, key errors, etc.)\\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\\n            \\\"Unexpected error in get_coordinates()\\\",\\n            error_detail=str(generic_err)\\n        )\\n\\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------\\n# 4\ufe0f\u20e3  Optional convenience wrapper \u2013 returns a dict instead of tuple\\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------\\ndef get_coordinates_dict(address: str) -> Dict[str, float]:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Same as get_coordinates but returns {'lat':\u2026, 'lng':\u2026}.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    lat, lng = get_coordinates(address)\\n    return {\\\"lat\\\": lat, \\\"lng\\\": lng}\\n```\\n\\n### What changed?\\n\\n| Line | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| **Exception class** | `error_detail` now has a default value (`None`). |\\n| **_get_api_key()** | Raises the exception with both arguments if the key is missing. |\\n| **get_coordinates()** | All `raise HolidayAgentException` calls now pass a second argument (`error_detail`). |\\n| **Broad `except` blocks** | Capture the original exception (`req_err` / `generic_err`) and forward its string representation. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f How to apply the fix\\n\\n1. **Open the file**  \\n   `C:\\\\AI_2026\\\\Projects\\\\1_TravelBot\\\\HolidayAgent\\\\Tools\\\\GoogleMap.py` in your editor (VS\u202fCode, PyCharm, Notepad++, etc.).\\n\\n2. **Replace** the existing content with the patched version above **or** edit the two sections highlighted (exception class & raise statements) to match the snippets.\\n\\n3. **Save** the file.\\n\\n4. **Clear the compiled cache** (Python may still be using the old `.pyc`):  \\n\\n   ```bash\\n   del /s /q C:\\\\AI_2026\\\\Projects\\\\1_TravelBot\\\\HolidayAgent\\\\Tools\\\\__pycache__\\\\*\\n   ```\\n\\n   *(or just delete the whole `__pycache__` folder).*\\n\\n5. **Restart** the HolidayAgent service / re\u2011run your script.\\n\\n6. **Test** the function:\\n\\n   ```python\\n   from HolidayAgent.Tools.GoogleMap import get_coordinates\\n   print(get_coordinates(\\\"Goa, India\\\"))\\n   ```\\n\\n   You should see something like:\\n\\n   ```\\n   (15.2993265, 74.1240123)\\n   ```\\n\\n   If an error occurs, you\u2019ll now get a clear `HolidayAgentException` that also prints the underlying `error_detail`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccc Common follow\u2011up issues & quick fixes  \\n\\n| Symptom | Likely cause | Quick fix |\\n|---------|--------------|-----------|\\n| `NameError: name 'e' is not defined` | You added `error_detail=str(e)` but the `except` clause is `except Exception:` (no `as e`). | Change to `except Exception as e:`. |\\n| Still seeing the same TypeError after the patch | The old `.pyc` is still being imported. | Delete `__pycache__` (step\u202f4) or run Python with `-B` flag to ignore caches. |\\n| \u201cGoogle Maps API key invalid\u201d appears in `error_detail` | The environment variable `GOOGLE_API_KEY` is missing or wrong. | Set it: `set GOOGLE_API_KEY=YOUR_KEY` (Windows) or `export GOOGLE_API_KEY=YOUR_KEY` (Linux/macOS). |\\n| Timeout on the request | Network/firewall blocks outbound HTTPS. | Test the endpoint with `curl` or a browser; open the port if you\u2019re behind a corporate firewall. |\\n| `HolidayAgentException: Geocoding API returned no results\u2026` | Address string is malformed or too vague. | Use a more specific address (e.g., `\\\"Baga Beach, Goa, India\\\"`). |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 Next steps for you\\n\\n1. **Apply the patch** (or the minimal changes) and verify the script runs.  \\n2. If you need **additional Google\u2011Maps\u2011related helpers** (e.g., distance matrix, place search, static map image), let me know \u2013 I can add them with the same robust error handling.  \\n3. Once the tool works, you can integrate it into the larger HolidayAgent workflow (e.g., auto\u2011generating itineraries with exact coordinates).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### TL;DR\\n\\n- **Make `error_detail` optional** in `HolidayAgentException` **or** always pass a second argument when raising it.  \\n- Delete `__pycache__` and restart the bot.  \\n- Test with a simple call to `get_coordinates()` \u2013 you should now get a proper result or a clear, informative exception.\\n\\nIf you run into any new traceback or need help extending the Google Maps wrapper, just drop the error message here and I\u2019ll walk you through the next fix. Happy coding! \ud83c\udf89\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"},\"inner_messages\":[]},\"name\":\"Travel_Planner\"}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_c5585e0a-0833-4e4d-a341-f77a11bf0c5b/c5585e0a-0833-4e4d-a341-f77a11bf0c5b", "receiver": null, "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.DELIVER", "type": "Message"}
